  "deferred": [
    {
      "kind": "guardrails",
      "reason": "Underwriting-domain policies (no appetite decision communicated to a broker before the human determination; declination notes must carry specific risk-based reasons; no E&S referral without the documented admitted-market declination; unfair-discrimination pattern watch on declines) require guardrail-service / OPA policy materialization, which Core does not expose as a pack surface yet. The behavioral core is partially covered today by Core invariants: every pack-configured agent is proposal-mode with four-eyes approval (agent-runtime), and the agent instructions + disposition taxonomy route final intake determinations exclusively to human analysts with the Underwriting Operations Manager as approver."
    },
    {
      "kind": "agent_recipes",
      "reason": "Bespoke LangGraph recipes (Submission Clearance Checker, Appetite Fit Scorer, Completeness Chaser, Renewal-Defense Deadline Sentinel) require agent-runtime graph-module registration (BRD 23 BR-12). This pack specializes the existing case-triage + analytics agents via TenantAgentConfig prompt_params + tenant-scope RAG grounding instead."
    },
    {
      "kind": "connection_templates",
      "reason": "Production read connectors (agency-management and broker-portal systems: Applied Epic, Vertafore AMS360; submission-intake email/ACORD extraction feeds; clearance systems; loss-run retrieval services; D&B/experian-style firmographic enrichment; cat-modeling exposure feeds) require customer credentials and pack-service connector materialization. The pack ships seed datasets in the exact landing shape; production connectors are configured through the product Data > Connections UI."
    },
    {
      "kind": "write_adapters",
      "reason": "Write adapters (record the clearance block/release in the clearance system, send the declination letter with documented reasons, issue the broker information request, open the underwriting file in the policy admin system, notify the surplus-lines broker on referral) execute only behind pack-service's materialization contract and customer credentials; every such write stays proposal-mode with human approval \u2014 no autonomous declination, referral, or broker communication, ever."
    },
    {
      "kind": "eval_sets",
      "reason": "Golden eval sets (clearance-conflict detection, appetite-fit calls, completeness gap identification, deadline-risk ranking) require eval-service write APIs whose action names are not yet in the rbac canonical catalog (Core follow-up noted in rbac catalog.go)."
    },
    {
      "kind": "ontology",
      "reason": "Ontology registration (Insured, Account, Submission, Broker, Brokerage, AppetiteStatement, LossRun, StatementOfValues, Application, ClearanceRecord, NeededByClock, DeclinationLetter) awaits pack-service; entity semantics are carried today by the underwriting_core semantic model and dataset schemas."
    },
    {
      "kind": "case_schemas",
      "reason": "Typed case schemas (submission_triage, clearance_conflict_review, appetite_referral, completeness_chase, renewal_defense) await case-service schema materialization; today's cases carry the same fields via display_projection + the disposition taxonomy."
    },
